These 72x72 PNGs are vendored unmodified (a curated single-codepoint subset)
by tools/emoji/fetch-twemoji.py so wm/pleromussy can render emoji as inline
images -- no Inferno font covers the emoji blocks.  File names follow the
twemoji convention: lowercase hex codepoint(s) joined by '-', with the U+FE0F
variation selector omitted.
